The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, April 30, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Friday, April 30, 2004				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Deshapriya Park, Rashbehari Avenue, Bijon Setu from 3 pm. Ananda Marga annual rally.				 																Interface				 																																	An interface with US film-maker Vismita Gupta-Smith, at Saathii Calcutta Resource Centre, CD-335, Salt Lake, at 5.30 pm. Her documentary For Straights Only will also be screened.				 																																	An interaction with Ruskin Bond at Crossword, at 3 pm.				 																Hard Talk				 																																	Subrata Bose, deputy manager of West Bengal Horticulture Development Corporation, will meet readers of The Telegraph at his office in Mayukh Bhavan, Salt Lake, at 6 pm. 				 																Music fiesta				 																																	Gary Lawyer will perform with city band Hip Pocket at Someplace Else, 9 pm onwards.				 																																	A presentation of Puratani Bengali songs by Ramkumar Chattopadhyay and his students at Gorky Sadan, 6 pm.				 																Screenings				 																																	Double Indemnity and documentary Film Noir will be screened at Nandan III, between 11.30 am and 3.20 pm. A discussion on Hollywood: yesterday, today, tomorrow will also be held. By invitation only.				 																Art watch				 																																	An exhibition of photographs, Borders and Beyond, on display at Seagull Arts amp; Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 7.30 pm.				 																																	Paintings and sculptures by artists of Andhra Pradesh on view at Samokal Gallery, on Gariahat Road, 2 pm to 8 pm.
